original: Josefson, Einar, tf. a&sessor, kapten, Göteborg, f. 20/7/05 i Gbg av Einar J. o. Tullia Josefson. G. 39 m. Solvind Lundgren. Barn: Hans f. 40, Annika 43, Per 45. — Stud:ex. 24, res:off:ex. 26, jur. kand. 33. Kapt. i Göta art:reg. res. 41. Tingstjg. i Askims, Hisings o. Sävedals dom-s. 33-36, tjg. i Göta hovr. 37-38, fiskals-förordn. 38, e. o. not. v. Gbgs magistrat o. rådhusr, 37, tf. assessor där (första förordn. 41). Lärare i fö.rf :kunsk. v. Na vig: sk. i Gbg 47. Övermarskalik f. Gbgs sted, Medl. av SHT 41. Hob-bies : språk, bok samlande.
translated: Josefson, Einar, acting assessor, captain, Gothenburg, b. 20/7/05 in Gothenburg to Einar J. and Tullia Josefson. Married in 1939 to Solvind Lundgren. Children: Hans b. 1940, Annika b. 1943, Per b. 1945. — Passed studentexamen in 1924, reserve officer examination in 1926, law degree in 1933. Captain in the Gotha artillery regiment from 1941. Judicial clerk in the Askims, Hisings and Sävedals district courts from 1933-1936, clerk in the Gothenburg court of appeal from 1937-1938, assistant notary public for the Gothenburg magistracy and council from 1937, acting assessor there (first appointed in 1941). Teacher in private law at the Naval School in Gothenburg in 1947. Chief marshal for Gothenburg, member of the Swedish Historical Society in 1941. Hobbies: language, book collecting.
